Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.39,0:00:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon returning from Munich,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.76,0:00:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,with Lotte in tow, her dad attended \Na party in Frau Gerlach's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.35,0:00:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There, Lotte, having taken a glance at dad's world \Nthat was obscured from her up until this day,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.47,0:00:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,starts to feel the crevice \Nbetween her and dad widening rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.77,0:00:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Before - the broken frame of mother's photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.53,0:00:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now - Frau Gerlach's imposed amicability. {I hope he means this by "repulsing/disgusting/unnatural close (e.g. friend); familiar; friendly; intimate" - either it's disgusting to lotte how she is being authoritative over dad, or how she is friendly to lotte who doesn't want to be her friend}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.45,0:00:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As Lotte feels being left out completely, \Na sharp pain runs through her little chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.48,0:00:34.49,Sign,,0,0,115,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 20 \N {\fs35} New Ally, Herr Gabele {新しい味方・ガベーレさん} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.72,0:00:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I tell her about all of this? {How should I write of it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.49,0:00:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The broken frame of mom's photo... \NI can't be entirely sure what had happened to it. {/I don't clearly understand}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.40,0:00:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But it may seriously trouble Luise if I tell her...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.64,0:00:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.50,0:00:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't hurry up now, \Nyou'll be late for school!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.63,0:01:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.67,0:01:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know what you mean, Peperl.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.62,0:01:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get ready now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.15,0:01:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, on my way from school, \NI'll try to drop by dad's atelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.65,0:01:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll thus learn something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.56,0:01:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The letter can wait until then, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.13,0:01:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right! I should also \Nwrite her about the painter next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.51,0:01:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, you've been through some torment, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.56,0:01:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I could tell by the Imp of Sorrow \Nsitting on your shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.54,0:01:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Imp of Sorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.10,0:01:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, with this fellow around, \Nyou'll never get your good night's sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.85,0:01:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. This Old Herr would look after him for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.02,0:01:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! He's caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.46,0:01:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There, you'll be fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.76,0:01:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Herr Gabele, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.14,0:01:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for that man, \Nwho knows if I would have gotten any sleep last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.87,0:02:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Should say my thanks, next time we meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.22,0:02:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that sounds a lot more like it. {masterpiece; best work}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.97,0:02:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I ought to give Frau Irene my thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.11,0:02:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The party yesterday \Nprovided for a fine change of mood. {change of pace; change of mood; (mental) break (e.g. going for a walk); refreshment}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.04,0:02:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.64,0:02:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? The frame is broken. \NHow did this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.10,0:02:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But the picture is intact. {/not damaged}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.47,0:03:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, our adorable Luise \Nis {\i1}your{\i0} daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.80,0:03:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,She had inherited that elegance of yours in full. {splendor; splendour; magnificence; beauty​}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.21,0:03:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I thank you and pray \Nthat the happiness follows you closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.16,0:03:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since that evening, \NI can't bring myself to talk to her directly about it. {/look straight/upfront in the face - not sure if he means "I can't make myself" or "I hadn't had a chance"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I swear, it takes an idiot \Nto make a drunk confession like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.17,0:03:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.72,0:03:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.47,0:03:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.67,0:03:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't feign ignorance! {to evade (a question, taxes, etc.); to dodge; to gloss over (a mistake, fault, etc.); to smooth over; to get one's way out of (a difficult situation); to explain away​} \NThe special project for the next issue!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:03:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How come you let Karl do it all by himself? {really hope this ka-ru is just some other journalist's name}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.24,0:03:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is {\i1}that{\i0} what you wanted to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.85,0:03:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This project has been {\i1}my{\i0} brainchild all along! 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.55,0:03:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, but look at it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.06,0:04:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"The path of a divorced woman."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't find a better writer for it! {/perfect}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.04,0:04:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the only one around \Nwho went through an actual divorce!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.63,0:04:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Well if it's all right with you, \Nthen of course, it must really be so. {unsure what he means, maybe "if you're fine with bringing it up, naturally I can allow you" or "if you say it's better this way, of course it's better this way" }
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.11,0:04:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter with you, Editor?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.33,0:04:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,For the last few days, \Nyou're constantly talking in a roundabout way. {to beat around the bush; to not speak frankly; to talk in a roundabout way​}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.24,0:04:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Recover sooner and become vocal and forthright again! {/like before, you should be ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.20,0:04:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Boisterous as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.40,0:04:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, I'm the only one here getting hung up on it. {/moreover, it's me who is worrying too much}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.70,0:04:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... A General Delivery letter from Vienna...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.70,0:04:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears, none today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.66,0:04:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.23,0:04:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.98,0:04:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, as soon as you're in Vienna, \Nyou'd send me a letter - that's what you said yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.05,0:05:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if dad is still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.08,0:05:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I could ask him directly about the photo?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.73,0:05:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if he even returned here last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.83,0:05:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Not here! \NThat photo frame...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.12,0:05:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was sure I left it somewhere here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.19,0:05:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the frame. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.83,0:05:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The photo is no longer in it... {/taken out}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.60,0:05:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It means, dad returned here, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.54,0:05:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, this...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.52,0:05:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But what became of the photo?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.41,0:06:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Not here... Could he have hidden it somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.47,0:06:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.56,0:06:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Our engagement is a matter of time... {I translated this as "It's still a long time before we're engaged" in ep 19, but now I think maybe it means the opposite thing, because that'd make more sense here}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.49,0:06:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.85,0:06:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.98,0:06:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don't know for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.62,0:06:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither about it, nor about dad marrying Frau Gerlach.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.28,0:06:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. It's not decided yet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.96,0:06:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise... Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.09,0:06:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What should i do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Peperl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.68,0:07:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.71,0:07:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You are my only consolation these days, Peperl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.48,0:07:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Gabele... I wonder what his room is like. {/where}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.05,0:07:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Peperl! Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.08,0:07:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Behave, Peperl. {/come back}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.72,0:07:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Peperl, you can't go there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.25,0:08:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Peperl!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.79,0:08:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do this to me, Peperl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.87,0:08:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you telling me, this here \Nis Herr Gabele's room?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.68,0:08:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.78,0:08:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Not home, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.08,0:08:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's return, Peperl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.59,0:08:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's open! I didn't lock the door. \NCome in whenever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.67,0:08:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure is an amiable pup, you. {friendly; affable; amiable; sociable; loving company; (animals) taking kindly to men}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.87,0:08:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't make a good watchdog this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.39,0:09:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Herr Gabele?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.27,0:09:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? A bit too soon for me \Nto be seeing angels. {/a visit from angel}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.26,0:09:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be last night's Fraulein.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.46,0:09:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. My name is Luise Palfy, Herr. \NI live in the house next to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.23,0:09:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.73,0:09:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You moved here when you were very little - like this. \NHowever, we never spoke until last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.51,0:09:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for what you did last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.68,0:09:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to it, I could sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.14,0:09:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's a relief to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.31,0:09:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now... I should offer Little Lady some tea...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.85,0:09:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Gabele, something happened to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.45,0:09:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, nothing. \NMaybe just caught a cold from strolling at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.36,0:09:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! You have a terrible fever!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.39,0:09:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind it, just some cold. \NNothing a good share of sleep can't cure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.40,0:09:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, if you see a doctor, maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.73,0:09:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fed up with doctors. \N They make a fuss over anything. {/don't do unnecessary things}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.70,0:09:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What about a meal?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.09,0:09:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine, I would gladly do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.46,0:10:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, return to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.19,0:10:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.34,0:10:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my, I thought you're a crybaby at first, \Nbut suddenly you're a real nurse!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.77,0:10:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.38,0:10:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Peperl, sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.21,0:10:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein, is there really any need to do all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.40,0:10:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he is ill, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.13,0:10:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He has a cold, a fever, and just feels drowsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.85,0:10:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In case of cold, the best treatment \Nis hot food and good sleep, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.63,0:10:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all true and stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.30,0:10:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But why be so attentive to some \Nsecond-rate painter you don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.20,0:10:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Gabele is a decent person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.54,0:11:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why he had also been attentive to me before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.79,0:11:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi, where's the medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.84,0:11:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Been there last time I checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.78,0:11:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But regardless, letting you go all alone \Ninto some oddball's room is a no-go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.06,0:11:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to bring me along.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.12,0:11:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.74,0:11:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's open!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.01,0:11:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for the wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.00,0:11:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got you a whole pot of hot soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.20,0:11:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have a meal now, then drink the medicine \Nand get all the sleep you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.93,0:11:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This would make anyone's cold vanish! {/blow away}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.71,0:11:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a special soup Fraulein made just for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.88,0:11:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to taste it thoroughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.88,0:11:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This here is Resi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.18,0:11:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She is a housekeeper living with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.34,0:11:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do you know, today is my lucky day!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.92,0:11:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately after Luise, \NI'm seeing another angel, armed with a broom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.86,0:11:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Angel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.89,0:11:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you suppose that could be me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.70,0:12:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There's this terrific glare to your personality \Nthat sends a painter's imagination soaring. {you have this amazing personality that tickles the senses of us painters}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.28,0:12:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact I'm feeling better already, I owe solely \Nto my determination to paint a picture with you as a model. {/when I get better}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.48,0:12:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, not in your life! \NBeing a model is embarrassing...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.98,0:12:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.36,0:12:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's a pity to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.88,0:12:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There, your meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.12,0:12:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is delightful!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.18,0:12:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It warms the body to the core!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.00,0:12:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But most of all - the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.13,0:12:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein, now that I think of it, \Nmaybe he is not that bad a person...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.77,0:12:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.48,0:12:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad didn't come home today either...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.17,0:13:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever I need to talk to him, \Ndad is never here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.79,0:13:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Was Luise also feeling that lonely here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.73,0:13:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,With mom, I could discuss anything, any time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.88,0:13:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right... A long time ago, \Nmom must have been feeling lonely, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.51,0:13:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.02,0:13:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't you do your work from home?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.67,0:13:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.98,0:13:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Fraulein Tiny Angel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.35,0:13:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, dear, my cold vanished just like you said. \NTo celebrate that, I figured I'd clean my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.95,0:13:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gone already? That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.12,0:13:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let me help you with that, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.43,0:14:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendidly done. \NWith your help, this place is mighty cleaner now! {lit: a good deal refreshed}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.16,0:14:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me thank you with tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.30,0:14:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a good many of your paintings stored up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.43,0:14:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm not selling those.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.01,0:14:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Or rather, I can't sell any of them anyways. {/or maybe it would be more precise to say they don't sell well}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.65,0:14:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this picture called? {dai is "title; subject; theme; topic" so maybe she means "what is ... called" or maybe "what it depicts"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.16,0:14:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be "Twilight of Gods." {/evening/twilight of gods/divine melancholia}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.29,0:14:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What is pictured on it? {/what were you trying to draw}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.73,0:14:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Good question! I was hoping you'd tell me. {I don't know myself}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.57,0:14:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's for later, \Nyou tea is getting cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.74,0:14:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bit convoluted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.23,0:14:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Gabele, you're not married?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.59,0:15:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you feel lonely?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.21,0:15:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a lot more relaxed, staying alone! \NCan just paint however I like it. {carefree; comfortable; at ease} {/draw pictures when/how I want/on my own volution}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.20,0:15:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Herr Gabele...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.56,0:15:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,For an artist, having a wife and kids \Nis a mere hindrance, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.23,0:15:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows. One always decides it for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.79,0:15:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For creatures such as artists, \Nthe happiness in its ordinary sense is unattainable anyway. {REALLY hope he means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.16,0:15:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The artist's idea of happiness is at odds with the idea \Nof happiness that an ordinary woman aspires for.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.48,0:15:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Herr Gabele, do you mean to say being able to paint \Nis more important than anything else to you? {/the most important thing is painting the pictures}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.18,0:15:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so. Perhaps, painting is the reason \Nwhy I've been born into this world, or so I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.56,0:15:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,For dad as well, \Nis music more important than anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.70,0:15:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Luise? \NSomething else is worrying you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.60,0:15:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as it's not a secret, \NI'm curious to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.96,0:16:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Gabele, will you hear me out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.41,0:16:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.73,0:16:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a friend, whose parents \Nbroke up a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.17,0:16:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Initially, she had a sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.18,0:16:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But upon parting, \Ndad and mom split their kids apart as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.50,0:16:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't until recently that them two \Nhad finally found out about each other. {/got to know each other}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.90,0:16:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, those two sisters decided to try \Nto get their parents make up and live together again. {/think it'll be good if ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.33,0:16:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you think of any good way to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.50,0:16:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy to understand how you feel, \Nbut it's not easy to solve that riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.47,0:16:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.03,0:16:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Marriage is never anything plain or straightforward.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.61,0:16:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The human emotions are a conundrum, \Nonly existing in an incomprehensible realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.84,0:16:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But if they broke up, \Nperhaps that's for the sake of everyone's happiness. {/if they chose to break up, it must be that they are happier this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.65,0:16:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.87,0:16:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if the two parents \Nstill love each other, even to this day?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.02,0:16:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, those sisters also act \Nfor the sake of the family's happiness, right? {lit is "those siblings have in mind a wish that their family lives together" but I don't see how it's connected to previous line}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.17,0:17:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there really nothing children can do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.18,0:17:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,After all...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.17,0:17:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,After all...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.15,0:17:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.77,0:17:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.94,0:17:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.92,0:17:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.91,0:17:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You are such a caring child, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.00,0:17:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, then! Why don't I join those sisters' cause as well? {/i too will support those sisters won't I}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.44,0:17:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try to advise you in any way I can. Don't hesitate \Nto tell Luise that she can count on my help as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.51,0:17:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.01,0:17:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Deal? Whatever befalls those sisters, this guy Gabele \Nis henceforth their faithful ally for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.47,0:17:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Herr Gabele.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.62,0:18:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, how about we focus \Non something brighter, for a change?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.85,0:18:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I might also have \Na certain favor to ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.80,0:18:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.43,0:18:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you tired?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.24,0:18:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.26,0:18:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting too dark here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.73,0:18:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the windows in your room are so small.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.17,0:18:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's about as bad \Nfor a painter's atelier as it can get.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.25,0:18:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You should try looking for a more suitable place!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.59,0:18:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are not thick on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.66,0:18:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you turn a bit more to the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.66,0:18:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, isn't it better for a painter's atelier \Nto also have a high ceiling?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.76,0:18:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if possible. {dekitara ne?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.47,0:18:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, the light that comes through big windows \Ncan come from above and lie evenly. {/comes from above. which is even better}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.64,0:18:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds an awful lot like dad's atelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.11,0:18:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.21,0:19:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Gabele, would you be allowed \Nto bring piano into this room? {lit is "do/can you play piano in this room" but I think she means like if his neighbours don't mind or something}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.28,0:19:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The fellow that lived here before me \Nwas a pianist, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need as much light for composing music \Nas you do for painting, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.13,0:19:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... You could do with less, I suppose. \NBut those questions... Something on your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.83,0:19:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.10,0:19:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. If dad and Herr Gabele exchange ateliers, \Nthat would only benefit everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.97,0:19:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If they do, nothing would stand in the way \Nof Herr Gabele's work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.22,0:19:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And dad also would be able \Nto return home at any moment! {/will return home immedieately}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.33,0:19:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we'll even start dining together!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.78,0:19:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the finest ideas I ever had!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.96,0:19:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.64,0:19:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Along with the tears she was shedding frantically,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.33,0:20:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte managed to expel from her chest \Nthat pain of the last few days. {/thing that was hurting her chest disappeared}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.89,0:20:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to finding a new ally in Herr Gabele, \NLotte had regained her spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.90,0:20:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How would she make use of this advantage, \Nas our story progresses?
Comment: 0,0:20:20.77,0:20:20.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.71,0:20:30.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.24,0:20:33.70,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.70,0:20:37.42,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.42,0:20:40.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.55,0:20:51.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.97,0:20:55.73,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.73,0:20:59.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.27,0:21:02.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.11,0:21:05.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.69,0:21:09.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.24,0:21:13.79,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.79,0:21:17.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.49,0:21:23.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.14,0:21:26.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.55,0:21:30.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.18,0:21:32.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.00,0:21:37.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.77,0:21:41.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:44.77,0:21:44.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.25,0:21:46.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.95,0:21:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, we're in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.82,0:21:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad told me, he is proposing to Frau Gerlach!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.86,0:21:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You can't let this happen! \NYou absolutely can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.46,0:22:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad has been completely alone \Never since he broke up with mom, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.06,0:22:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, I think he had decided \Nhe no longer wants to be alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.32,0:22:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, you must at any cost prevent that marriage \Nfrom coming to fruition! I believe in you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.70,0:22:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.54,0:22:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, Don't Get Married! {お父さん結婚しないで}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.44,0:22:15.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 21\NDad, Don't Get Married! {お父さん結婚しないで}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.81,0:22:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Look forward to it!
